    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4b48c6fd_012e6c40",
        "filename": "android/metrics/IniFileAutoFlusher.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 44,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-12T23:41:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It\u0027s not a bug, more a feature :)\nQEMU picks the timer and copies the variables under the lock and then releases it - so the callback is able to call timer-related functions without deadlocking. But this also means anyone else might call those right between releasing the lock and calling the callback:\n\n  cb \u003d timer-\u003ecb;\n  user_data \u003d timer-\u003euser_data;\n  remove_timer_from_pending(timer);\n  unlock();\n    \u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c\u003c right here\n  cb(user_data);\n\nThere\u0027s no simple way of making sure the timer is still alive here",
      "parentUuid": "0bfc0e7c_cc704f15",
      "revId": "14c3a1bd44ac6f7a31a4accca63c0ea5e1308636",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8baf1e8f_ccfa2f86",
        "filename": "android/metrics/IniFileAutoFlusher.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 67,
      "author": {
        "id": 1099352
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-12T18:34:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why do we only delete the weakPtr when we can\u0027t lock it?  Seems to me that it\u0027s also dead if the callback gets called -- that this method has ownership of the WeakPtr object.  Maybe a unique_ptr\u003cWeakPtr\u003e at the top, to ensure destruction in both cases?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 67,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 67,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "14c3a1bd44ac6f7a31a4accca63c0ea5e1308636",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4b48c6fd_a16538ab",
        "filename": "android/metrics/IniFileAutoFlusher.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 67,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-12T23:41:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "if we lock the pointer, reschedule the timer to run again and then release the shared pointer. This means the next callback run would need to start with locking it again",
      "parentUuid": "8baf1e8f_ccfa2f86",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 67,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 67,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "14c3a1bd44ac6f7a31a4accca63c0ea5e1308636",
